pullRequest.body:
---

Perhaps the worst De Bruijn factor I have ever seen, 10 lines of pen-and-paper proof turning into 575 lines of Lean code. I could probably split this file into multiple PRs, but there isn't really a point given that everything in the file except for the last two definition should be considered an implementation detail.

There is some relevant discussion here: https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/pull/10244#discussion_r1477365199
